// C2: Acting Components
instance PermanentMagnetSynchronousMotor : DTDFVocab:ActingComponent [
    base:desc "Primary drive mechanism for the first axis of MABI MAX industrial robot, controlled via Siemens SINUMERIK 840D sl industrial controller. Constrained by mechanical limits (torque, speed, acceleration) and safety protocols enforced by the controller."
]

instance SiemensSinumerik840DslController : DTDFVocab:ActingComponent [
    base:desc "Industrial controller interfacing with PermanentMagnetSynchronousMotor to regulate motion profiles. Implements safety protocols and receives real-time feedback from sensing components for dynamic adjustment of actuation range."
]

instance IndustrialCommunicationInterface : DTDFVocab:ActingComponent [
    base:desc "Remote control interface enabling integration with Digital Twin simulation and monitoring layers via industrial communication protocols (Ethernet/IP or PROFINET). Facilitates low-latency bidirectional communication for closed-loop control capabilities."
]

// C3: Physical Sensing Components
instance MotorShaftPositionEncoder : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "17-bit incremental encoder mounted directly on PermanentMagnetSynchronousMotor shaft for high-resolution absolute position tracking. Sampling frequency aligned with motor dynamics (1-10 kHz)."
    DTDFVocab:producedData MotorShaftPositionData
]

instance GearboxPositionEncoder : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "17-bit incremental encoder positioned behind gearbox for high-resolution position tracking with minimized backlash. Sampling frequency aligned with motor dynamics (1-10 kHz)."
    DTDFVocab:producedData GearboxPositionData
]

instance MotorPhaseCurrentSensor : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Current sensor measuring motor phase currents for torque estimation using known motor constants (torque constant Kt). Integrated with SiemensSinumerik840DslController for real-time feedback."
    DTDFVocab:producedData MotorPhaseCurrentData
]

// C4: Physical-to-Virtual Data Transmission
instance MotorShaftPositionData : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom MotorShaftPositionEncoder
    base:desc "Real-time position data transmitted from MotorShaftPositionEncoder to Digital Twin via MQTT protocol with 1ms latency for closed-loop control integration."
]

instance GearboxPositionData : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom GearboxPositionEncoder
    base:desc "Real-time position data transmitted from GearboxPositionEncoder to Digital Twin via MQTT protocol with 1ms latency for redundancy and fault tolerance."
]

instance MotorPhaseCurrentData : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom MotorPhaseCurrentSensor
    base:desc "Real-time current data transmitted from MotorPhaseCurrentSensor to Digital Twin via MQTT protocol for torque estimation and dynamic control adjustments."
]

// C10: Models/Data
instance SysMLInternalBlockDiagram : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "SysML IBD representing MABI MAX first axis components, connectors, and interfaces following MBSE RFLP methodology. Captures structural architecture for requirements→functional→logical→physical layers."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo SysMLModelingTool
]

instance SimulinkFrictionModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "Executable MATLAB Simulink model for dynamic behavior analysis of first axis friction. Implements state-based or automaton-driven simulations for predictive maintenance and diagnostic purposes."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo SimulinkExecutionEngine
]

instance ContextualDataTrace : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Aggregated and abstracted sensor data traces from physical system following Digital Shadow Reference Model. Includes position, torque, and current data for friction loss detection and operational analysis."
    DTDFVocab:fromData MotorShaftPositionData, GearboxPositionData, MotorPhaseCurrentData
    DTDFVocab:inputTo DataAggregationEngine
]

instance FrictionLossDatabase : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Historical friction loss data repository populated from ContextualDataTrace for trend analysis and predictive maintenance algorithms."
    DTDFVocab:fromData ContextualDataTrace
    DTDFVocab:inputTo MaintenanceAnalysisEngine
]

// C11: Enablers
instance SysMLModelingTool : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "SysML v1.7 modeling tool enabling Internal Block Diagrams and state machines for component-based system architecture modeling of MABI MAX first axis."
    DTDFVocab:enables SysMLArchitectureService, SysMLSimulationService
]

instance SimulinkExecutionEngine : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "MATLAB Simulink runtime environment executing SimulinkFrictionModel for real-time dynamic behavior simulation and control logic validation."
    DTDFVocab:enables SimulinkSimulationService, ControlLogicValidationService
]

instance MQTTProtocolStack : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "MQTT-based communication protocol stack enabling real-time streaming of DataTransmitted instances from physical components to Digital Twin with 1ms latency."
    DTDFVocab:enables DataStreamingService, RemoteControlInterface
]

instance DataAggregationEngine : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Contextual data aggregation framework implementing Digital Shadow Reference Model for one-way data flow from physical system to digital representation."
    DTDFVocab:enables DataAnalysisService, DigitalShadowService
]

instance MaintenanceAnalysisEngine : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Predictive maintenance analysis engine processing FrictionLossDatabase for anomaly detection and maintenance scheduling recommendations."
    DTDFVocab:enables PredictiveMaintenanceService, MaintenanceRecommendationService
]

// C6: Services
instance SysMLArchitectureService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service providing SysML model visualization and component relationship analysis for system engineering teams."
    DTDFVocab:provides ArchitectureVisualizationInsight
]

instance SysMLSimulationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service enabling SysML model simulation for behavioral validation against requirements."
    DTDFVocab:provides SimulationValidationInsight
]

instance SimulinkSimulationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service executing SimulinkFrictionModel for dynamic behavior analysis and control logic testing."
    DTDFVocab:provides DynamicBehaviorInsight
]

instance ControlLogicValidationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service validating control logic against physical system constraints using Simulink simulations."
    DTDFVocab:provides ControlValidationInsight
]

instance DataStreamingService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service managing real-time data transmission from physical components to Digital Twin via MQTT protocol."
    DTDFVocab:provides DataTransmissionInsight
]

instance RemoteControlInterface : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service enabling remote control and monitoring of MABI MAX through industrial communication protocols."
    DTDFVocab:provides RemoteMonitoringInsight
]

instance DataAnalysisService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service processing ContextualDataTrace for pattern recognition and operational trend analysis."
    DTDFVocab:provides OperationalAnalysisInsight
]

instance DigitalShadowService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service implementing passive digital shadow methodology for one-way data aggregation from physical system."
    DTDFVocab:provides ShadowRepresentationInsight
]

instance PredictiveMaintenanceService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service analyzing FrictionLossDatabase for predictive maintenance recommendations."
    DTDFVocab:provides MaintenancePredictionInsight
]

instance MaintenanceRecommendationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service generating maintenance action plans based on predictive analysis results."
    DTDFVocab:provides MaintenanceActionInsight
]

// C17: Insights/Actions
instance ArchitectureVisualizationInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Visual representation of MABI MAX first axis architecture including components, connectors, and interfaces for system engineering validation."
]

instance SimulationValidationInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Results from SysML model simulations validating compliance with functional requirements."
]

instance DynamicBehaviorInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Dynamic behavior analysis of first axis friction using Simulink simulations for control performance evaluation."
]

instance ControlValidationInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Validation results comparing simulated control logic against physical system constraints."
]

instance DataTransmissionInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Metrics on real-time data transmission quality including latency, packet loss, and data integrity."
]

instance RemoteMonitoringInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Live monitoring data from MABI MAX first axis including position, torque, and current parameters."
]

instance OperationalAnalysisInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Operational trend analysis identifying patterns in ContextualDataTrace for performance optimization."
]

instance ShadowRepresentationInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Digital shadow representation quality metrics including data completeness and temporal accuracy."
]

instance MaintenancePredictionInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Predictive maintenance forecasts including failure probability and remaining useful life estimates."
]

instance MaintenanceActionInsight : DTDFVocab:Action [
    base:desc "Maintenance action plans including recommended interventions and timing based on predictive analysis."
    DTDFVocab:IsAutomatic false
]

// C18: Environment
instance MabiMaxFirstAxisEnvironment : DTDFVocab:Environment [
    base:desc "Operational environment for MABI MAX first axis including physical components and their interactions."
    base:contains PermanentMagnetSynchronousMotor, SiemensSinumerik840DslController,
                MotorShaftPositionEncoder, GearboxPositionEncoder, MotorPhaseCurrentSensor,
                IndustrialCommunicationInterface
]

instance DigitalTwinSimulationEnvironment : DTDFVocab:Environment [
    base:desc "Virtual environment hosting Digital Twin models and simulations for analysis and validation."
    base:contains SysMLInternalBlockDiagram, SimulinkFrictionModel, ContextualDataTrace,
                FrictionLossDatabase
]

instance virtual_to_physical_interaction : DTDFVocab:VirtualToPhysical [
    base:desc "The document explicitly states that a **digital shadow** (closely related to the Digital Twin concept discussed) is characterized by a **one-way data flow from physical to digital**, with **no bidirectional or control flow from digital to physical**. Thus, **virtual-to-physical interaction does not exist** in this system as described. The text clarifies that digital shadows (and by extension, the Digital Twin framework referenced) **do not push data back to the physical system** or operate autonomously in control loops."
]

instance life_cycle_stages : DTDFVocab:EvolutionStage [
    base:desc "The lifecycle of a Digital Twin (DT) system is structured through **Model-Based Systems Engineering (MBSE)** methodologies, which decompose system modeling into hierarchical abstraction layers: **requirements, functional architecture, logical architecture, and product/technical layers**. Transition management between phases is facilitated by **architecture description languages (ADLs)** such as **ACME, AADL, MontiArc, or SysML Internal Block Diagrams (IBDs)**, which define component-connector perspectives, interfaces, and interconnections. Behavior modeling at the logical and product layers integrates **state machines (SysML v1.7), MontiArc Automaton, or simulation tools** (e.g., MathWorks Simulink, general-purpose languages like C++/Java). Lifecycle governance involves **heterogeneous stakeholder integration** and **multi-tool interoperability**, addressing complexity through methodologies like **RFLP (Requirements-Functions-Logics-Physics), OOSEM, SPES, or SMArDT**. The lifecycle transitions from abstract conceptual models to executable simulations, ensuring traceability and consistency across phases via **formalized modeling notations and toolchains**."
]

instance dt_technical_connection : DTDFVocab:TechnicalConnection [
    base:desc "The technical network infrastructure for the Digital Twin system is not explicitly detailed in the provided documents. However, the **one-way data flow** from physical to digital is facilitated via **MQTT**, which is mentioned as a communication protocol for data streaming. No further specifications on network topology, bandwidth, latency, redundancy, or security protocols (e.g., TLS, VPN) are provided. The document does not discuss bidirectional communication or control flows, nor does it elaborate on the underlying network architecture beyond the use of MQTT for data aggregation."
]

instance horizontal_integration : DTDFVocab:HoriIntegration [
    base:desc "The provided documents do not explicitly discuss horizontal integration with external systems, interoperability standards, or data exchange protocols for a Digital Twin system. However, the document mentions **MQTT** as a protocol for sensor data streaming in a specific robot use case (e.g., real-time identification of friction models in manufacturing). This suggests potential integration with external sensor networks or IoT systems, though no broader enterprise-level integration patterns (e.g., OPC UA, REST APIs, or service-oriented architectures) are described. The context remains limited to a single digital shadow for a robot axis, with no mention of multi-system coordination or standardized interoperability frameworks."
]

instance standardization : DTDFVocab:Standardization [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin system adheres to **industry standards** for **modeling and architecture description**, including **SysML (ISO/IEC 24744)**, **AADL (ISO/IEC 24764)**, and **ACME (OMG standard)** for component-connector modeling. **Interoperability standards** are implied through **heterogeneous tool integration** (e.g., SysML + Simulink + general-purpose languages), though explicit protocols (e.g., OPC UA, ROS 2) are not mentioned. **Compliance frameworks** are not detailed, but the use of **formalized ADLs and MBSE methodologies** suggests alignment with **systems engineering standards** (e.g., INCOSE’s SEBoK). **Certification requirements** are not specified, but the reliance on **standardized modeling languages** ensures traceability and reproducibility for regulatory or industry-specific validation."
]

instance security_and_safety_considerations : DTDFVocab:SecuritySafety [
    base:desc "
The digital shadow system for the MABI MAX 100 serial robot incorporates multiple safety and security measures tailored to its mechanical and control architecture. The **safety cell** physically restricts the operational range of the first axis to [-90°, 90°], enforcing positional constraints to prevent collisions or unsafe movements. The **dual encoder system** (motor encoder and secondary encoder behind the gearbox) mitigates positional uncertainty by enabling backlash compensation and real-time elasticity/friction analysis of the drive train, thereby enhancing kinematic accuracy and safety. The **Siemens SINUMERIK 840D sl CNC controller** enforces speed limits (|q̇_max| = 75°/s) and provides closed-loop control of position, speed, and acceleration, ensuring deterministic and safe motion profiles. Torque monitoring via motor current (I_M) and gearbox torque outputs (τ_G, τ_out) enables fault detection for overloading or mechanical failure. While the document does not explicitly mention cybersecurity protocols or formal risk assessments, the system’s **fail-safe design principles** are implicitly embedded in its hardware redundancy (dual encoders), controller constraints, and physical safety cell. The use of **known motor constants** for torque conversion from current further supports predictable and safe operation within defined operational envelopes."
]